<item>
            <title>[QPID-7964] [Java Client, AMQP 0-x] SCRAM SASL implementation incorrectly encodes &quot;=&quot; and &quot;,&quot; for passwords</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-7964</link>
                <project id="12310520" key="QPID">Qpid</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the Qpid Client for Java for AMQP 0-x encodes the characters &quot;=&quot; and &quot;,&quot; in passwords when using the SCRAM SASL mechanism.&lt;br/&gt;
This is incorrect. &lt;a href=&quot;https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5802&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;The spec&lt;/a&gt; requires encoding of those characters for the username. Not for the password.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was reported on the &lt;a href=&quot;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/qpid-users/201710.mbox/%3C1507290028737-0.post%40n2.nabble.com%3E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;user mailing list&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
