&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-7964&quot; title=&quot;[Java Client, AMQP 0-x] SCRAM SASL implementation incorrectly encodes &amp;quot;=&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;,&amp;quot; for passwords&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;QPID-7964&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;QPID-7964&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Java Client, AMQP 0-x&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; In SCRAM SASL implementation do not incorrectly encode &quot;=&quot; and &quot;,&quot; for passwords&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16243818" author="lorenz.quack" created="Wed, 8 Nov 2017 12:37:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The fix and tests were adapted from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPIDJMS-335&quot; title=&quot;SCRAM-SHA mechanism impls erroneously escape &amp;quot;=&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;,&amp;quot; in the password during processing&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;QPIDJMS-335&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;QPIDJMS-335&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16249557" author="k-wall" created="Mon, 13 Nov 2017 13:38:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Change and new tests looks good. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
